# Welcome to AIClient Documentation

AIClient is a lightweight, fully-featured JavaScript client for interacting with the Pollinations AI API. It enables you to generate text and images, manage retries, control seeds for reproducibility, and handle conversation history in an organized and reliable way.

This guide provides everything you need to start using AIClient in any web environment.

## Features
- Text generation with system prompts for guidance.
- Image generation with configurable dimensions.
- Retry logic for reliable request handling.
- Optional seeding for reproducible outputs.
- History management for text conversations.

## Starter Example
Below is a full HTML example demonstrating how to include AIClient via a CDN, initialize it, and generate text or images interactively.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>AIClient Starter Example</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: sans-serif; margin: 20px; }
    textarea { width: 100%; height: 80px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    button { margin-right: 5px; }
    #outputText { margin-top: 10px; white-space: pre-wrap; }
    #outputImage { max-width: 400px; display: block; margin-top: 10px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>AIClient Starter Example</h1>
<textarea id="prompt" placeholder="Enter your prompt here"></textarea>
<button id="generateText">Generate Text</button>
<button id="generateImage">Generate Image</button>
<div id="outputText"></div>
<img id="outputImage" />

<!-- Include AIClient via CDN -->
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/HyperRushNet/hrn-ai/client/1.0.3.min.js"></script>
<script>
  // Initialize AIClient
  const client = new AIClient()
    .setApiKey('YOUR_API_KEY')      // REQUIRED: your personal API key
    .setModel('flux')               // REQUIRED: model name
    .setSystemPrompt('You are a helpful assistant.') // optional for text
    .setTimeout(30000)              // optional, default 30000ms
    .setRetry(true, 2, 1000);       // optional retry logic

  // Generate text
  document.getElementById('generateText').addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const prompt = document.getElementById('prompt').value;
    if (!prompt) return alert('Please enter a prompt');
    client.setType('text');
    try {
      const text = await client.generate(prompt);
      document.getElementById('outputText').innerText = text;
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
      alert('Error generating text');
    }
  });

  // Generate image
  document.getElementById('generateImage').addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const prompt = document.getElementById('prompt').value;
    if (!prompt) return alert('Please enter a prompt');
    client.setType('image').setDimensions(512, 512);
    try {
      const blob = await client.generate(prompt);
      const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
      document.getElementById('outputImage').src = url;
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
      alert('Error generating image');
    }
  });
</script>
</body>
</html>
```

This starter example demonstrates:
- Including the library via CDN.
- Initializing the client with API key, model, timeout, and optional system prompt.
- Generating text and image outputs interactively.
- Displaying outputs in the page with minimal UI.

